                            The Balancing Act
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            Software developers are caught in an eternal cycle of balancing <strong>Architecture Velocity</strong> against <strong>Future-Proofing</strong>.
                        </p>
                        <div class="clay-callout">
                            <strong>Steve Smith's Reflection:</strong><br>
                            <em>&ldquo;Clean Architecture has higher upfront costs but offers lower long-term maintenance friction. Vertical Slices grant rapid initial velocity but require strict logical boundaries to prevent spaghetti code as domains expand.&rdquo;</em>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            Choosing the correct blueprint should not be a dogmatic battle. Real-world solutions prioritize decoupling hot path workflows into high-velocity modules while preserving a clean core domain.
                        </p>
